---

### View Architecture

Four views render into `.cal-pane`. The right panel renders independently and reacts to the same state.
```
SchedulerCore.state
  ├── currentView    'today' | 'day' | 'week' | 'month'
  ├── currentDate    Luxon DateTime (timezone-aware)
  ├── appointments   filtered array
  ├── providers      array
  └── visibleProviders  Set<number>
        │
        ├──► CalPane.render(state)   → writes to #cal-pane
        └──► RightPanel.render(state) → writes to #right-panel-body
Both panels receive the same state object and render independently. They never share DOM mutation — CalPane writes left, RightPanel writes right, no cross-contamination.

